Step 1: Create Flask App Files
Create a folder called flask-app-github and add the following:
app.py : 
-----
from flask import Flask

app = Flask(__name__)

@app.route('/')
def home():
    return "Welcome to my Flask app on GitHub!"

if __name__ == '__main__':
    app.run(debug=True)
-----


requirements.txt
------
Flask==2.2.5
------


README.md(if asked/optional)
-----
# Flask GitHub App ðŸš€

This is a simple Python Flask application pushed to GitHub.

## âœ… How to Run

```bash
